S
\bigtriangleup ABC
S = \dfrac{1}{2} \cdot ab \cdot sinC
H
BC
AH
BC
h = AH
S = \dfrac{1}{2}\cdot AH \cdot BC = \dfrac{1}{2} \cdot h \cdot BC = \dfrac{1}{2} \cdot (b\cdot sinC)\cdot a = \dfrac{1}{2} \cdot ab \cdot sinC
4S = 2\cdot ab \cdot sinC
sinC = \dfrac{c}{2R}
4S = 2 \cdot ab \cdot \dfrac{c}{2R} = \dfrac{abc}{R}
4R\cdot S_{\bigtriangleup ABC} = abc
